i have a driving phobia i can drive around town no problem unless it's in undiscovered parts of town i have occasionally driven as much as miles and nothing happened it is a problem for me i have a brand new suv but i always feel like something could happen and then what would i do i have had to pull off to the side of the road to cry driving any distance is so scary for me i'm and have been like this since i got my license at age and they made me get a license does anyone else have a similar problem there is only one true fear and we disguise it in many many ways the true fear is losing control of the situation it is evident in the then what would i do comment there are trained pros to help you with the what would i do they are called police officers and they are there to protect and serve you they can help with directions panic attacks and help you to get back on your way safely they can also help call a tow truck i am scared to drive as well and i know it i make it a point to drive somewhere everyday i take my time i have great maps and atlases and a cell phone and a road club membership i also practise deep breathing exercise and i tell my friends whan i need help i have never had any friend say no i also have a sense of humor just the other day i was near to tears because i could not figure out the traffic pattern i drove right past the building i was supposed to get to and once again was on the scenic route i laughed at the fact that i didn't explode i didn't die on the spot and i wasn't even late everyone is a little bit afraid of driving no one wants to get lost or broke down it is just that your reaction to these fears is a little overblown take heart you are not alone i celebrate everytime i drive somewhere new becuase my world just got a little bigger Panic attack Shaggy dog story Anxiety Time Out of Mind Minor characters in Teen Titans (animated series) Driver's license Ocean's Twelve Vegeta Piccolo Junior Saga Road West Side Highway Surveillance Similar